# Google OAuth 2.0 Desktop client credentials.
# Obtain from Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials → OAuth 2.0
# Client IDs (must be type "Desktop application"). The Gmail API must also be
# enabled for the same Cloud project.
#
# Both values are required by Google's Desktop OAuth flow. Google's docs state
# the client_secret for Desktop clients is not truly secret — it's embeddable
# in distributed binaries by design. We use PKCE on top to add per-flow
# protection (an intercepted auth code can't be exchanged without the
# matching code_verifier even if the secret is leaked).
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values.
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret
